tal existence in a time of generalized crisis. Her method, which emphasizes the material histories and uneven effects of capitalist development, models a unique critical approach to understanding the causes and conditions of ongoing biospheric catastrophe.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aAmerican poetryy20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aAmerican poetryy21st centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aEcology in literature. 0aEnvironmentalism in literature. 0aNature in literature. 4aAmerican poetry. 4aGreat Acceleration. 4aecocriticism. 4aend of nature. 4anatural history. 4aobsolescence. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311070368940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781503604896zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503604896423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503604896.jpg  a978-3-11-070368-9  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles